The Governors of New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, and Connecticut have announced a data-sharing agreement to share crime gun data across state lines. This agreement recognizes the need for a multijurisdictional approach to tackling gun violence, as firearms often cross state lines. President Biden supports this collaboration to address the public health epidemic of gun violence. In line with this, the Justice Department has launched five multijurisdictional firearms trafficking strike forces to target significant firearms trafficking corridors that have supplied guns to New York and other major cities. The article encourages other state and local officials to collaborate in reducing gun violence.